dropbear(8)



NNAAMMEE
       dropbear - lightweight SSH2 server

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ddrrooppbbeeaarr [-FEmwsgjki] [-b
       _b_a_n_n_e_r] [-d _d_s_s_k_e_y] [-r
       _r_s_a_k_e_y] [-p _p_o_r_t]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       ddrrooppbbeeaarr  is  a  SSH 2 server
       designed to be small enough to be used in small memory
       environments, while  still  being  functional  and
       secure enough for general use.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --bb _b_a_n_n_e_r
              bannerfile.  Display the contents of the file
              _b_a_n_n_e_r before user login (default:
              none).

       --dd _d_s_s_k_e_y
              dsskeyfile.  Use the contents of the file
              _d_s_s_k_e_y  for  the  dss host  key
              (default: /etc/dropbear/dropbear_dss_host_key).
              This file is generated with
              ddrrooppbbeeaarrkkeeyy(8).

       --rr _r_s_a_k_e_y
              rsakeyfile.  Use the contents of the file
              _r_s_a_k_e_y  for  the  rsa host  key
              (default: /etc/dropbear/dropbear_rsa_host_key).
              This file is generated with
              ddrrooppbbeeaarrkkeeyy(8).

       --FF     Don't fork into background.

       --EE     Log to standard error rather than syslog.

       --mm     Don't display the message of the day
       on login.

       --ww     Disallow root logins.

       --ss     Disable password logins.

       --gg     Disable password logins for root.

       --jj     Disable local port forwarding.

       --kk     Disable remote port forwarding.

       --pp _p_o_r_t
              Listen on specified tcp port _p_o_r_t;
              up to  10  can  be  specified (default 22 if
              none specified).

       --ii     Service  program  mode.   Use  this option
       to run ddrrooppbbeeaarr under
              TCP/IP servers like inetd, tcpsvd,  or
              tcpserver.   In  program mode the -F option is
              implied, and -p options are ignored.

       --aa     Allow remote hosts to connect to forwarded
       ports.

AAUUTTHHOORR
       Matt Johnston (matt@ucc.asn.au).  Gerrit Pape
       (pape@smarden.org) wrote this manual page.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       dropbearkey(8), dbclient(1)

       http://matt.ucc.asn.au/dropbear/dropbear.html



